modules.description: This module implements SPARQL protocol HTTP bindings using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. It provides `get` and `post` operations to send SPARQL queries to remote endpoints, handling request headers, graph context, and response parsing based on content type. It works with RDF graphs, IRIs, and SPARQL protocol messages, returning parsed results or error responses from SPARQL servers.

This module implements HTTP bindings for interacting with a 4Store RDF database using Lwt for asynchronous operations. It provides functions to execute SPARQL queries (select, ask, describe) via GET, perform SPARQL updates (insert, delete) via POST, and manage graph data through PUT, POST-append, and DELETE operations. It works directly with RDF graphs, IRIs, and SPARQL protocol messages, handling data manipulation and retrieval over HTTP.
